            <ns0:div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#martaf #AA">
                <ns0:p>Epaphrodeitos lived for 60 years.</ns0:p>
            </ns0:div>
            <ns0:div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#martaf">
                <ns0:p>Epaphrodeitos visse 60 anni.</ns0:p>
            </ns0:div>
            <ns0:div type="commentary">
                <ns0:p>Korhonen considers the inscription not urban because of the structure of the epitaph and the palaeography. Moreover, the name of the deceased, <ns0:foreign xml:lang="grc">&#7960;&#960;&#945;&#966;&#961;&#972;&#948;&#953;&#964;&#959;&#962;</ns0:foreign>, is highly attested in Sicily (see LGPN 3A: 145) and in another inscription from Catania (Libertini 1937: 78).</ns0:p>
            </ns0:div>
